    An array base queue implementation. This queue orders elements FIFO (first-in-first-out). The first element of the queue is that element that has been on the queue the longest time. The last element of the queue is that element that has been on the queue the shortest time. New elements are inserted at the tail of the queue, and the queue retrieval operations obtain elements at the head of the queue.
